Can you hear me?

45:49.917 --> 45:51.251
Behold thy mother.

46:02.638 --> 46:04.097
You must listen to me.

46:04.932 --> 46:06.934
You will not die for nothing.

46:11.688 --> 46:13.106
Oh, you tell your son...

46:15.317 --> 46:18.028
he wants to show me hell,
I ain't afraid of a little fire.

46:20.531 --> 46:21.823
He died for you.

46:24.493 --> 46:25.577
For Stephen.

47:15.794 --> 47:20.424
There was significant trauma to the head,
and vital organs. He's in a coma.

47:20.507 --> 47:22.426
If there's anyone
you'd like to see him again,

47:22.509 --> 47:24.428
I suggest you arrange that now.

47:24.511 --> 47:25.511
I...

47:26.555 --> 47:28.390
already lost one kid.

47:29.683 --> 47:32.895
They say lightning
don't strike the same place twice.

47:33.478 --> 47:35.772
The nurse can recommend a grief counselor.

48:06.553 --> 48:08.514
- God bless.
- Bye, Miss Carmen.

48:08.597 --> 48:09.890
- Bye.
- See you next Sunday.

48:41.505 --> 48:45.133
You got some kind of spell in there
gonna bring him back?

48:46.093 --> 48:48.595
It's just a prayer
for Mary's intercession.

48:48.679 --> 48:53.392
She don't give a good goddamn
about a real mother's son.

48:56.144 --> 48:57.771
You should get some rest.

48:58.897 --> 49:00.524
I could stay with him.

49:05.612 --> 49:06.947
His eyes are moving.

49:07.656 --> 49:09.366
What? Doctor!

49:11.034 --> 49:12.578
Stuart, baby.

49:13.161 --> 49:14.413
Can you hear me?

49:31.471 --> 49:32.890
Can you squeeze my hand?

49:34.600 --> 49:36.518
He's starting to come out of it.

49:57.122 --> 49:58.624
Damn thing ate my dollar.

50:00.626 --> 50:04.254
As if folks in here ain't paid enough,
you gotta bleed their pockets too.

50:06.173 --> 50:08.634
- Ain't you brought your own beverage?
- Son of a...

50:09.343 --> 50:11.428
- Where you going?
- What's it to you?

50:11.512 --> 50:13.597
Your mother told me you were dying.
What the fuck?

50:14.181 --> 50:15.807
You sound disappointed.

50:15.891 --> 50:19.269
Well, I took off work to be here.
You seem all right.

50:20.062 --> 50:21.063
Wait up, Stu.

50:23.232 --> 50:24.733
I forgot to give you this.

50:26.443 --> 50:28.362
St. Joseph. For the operation.

50:29.404 --> 50:30.405
Who's this?

50:30.989 --> 50:31.990
Who's asking?

50:32.074 --> 50:33.074
Stu's dad.

50:34.743 --> 50:36.995
I'm Carmen, Stuart's girlfriend.

50:37.913 --> 50:39.540
She know you're an atheist?

50:41.917 --> 50:43.377
He's baptized.

50:46.672 --> 50:49.466
He ain't dead.
He can speak for himself. Is that true?

50:52.094 --> 50:53.094
Yeah.

50:58.267 --> 51:00.602
- You know St. Stephen?
- Of course.

51:00.686 --> 51:02.938
Patron Saint of coffin makers.

51:03.480 --> 51:06.733
There's pictures of him
with a big pile of rocks on his head.

51:07.317 --> 51:08.151
Who'd have thought,

51:08.235 --> 51:10.696
you give your boy a nice Christian name,

51:12.072 --> 51:13.615
in a world full of fruits and nuts,

51:13.699 --> 51:15.993
you'd sentence him
to live right on up to it?

51:16.535 --> 51:17.744
Or down, as it were.

51:18.704 --> 51:19.746
Into the ground.

51:19.830 --> 51:21.456
That ain't how names work.

51:25.752 --> 51:27.212
Let me drive you home, Mr. Long.

51:27.296 --> 51:29.673
Hey, you got yourself a worrier.

51:32.676 --> 51:35.053
God will put me where he wants me to be.

51:35.137 --> 51:37.181
What's it to you
if I'm in hell or Hermosillo?

51:37.264 --> 51:38.264
"Sillo."

51:38.891 --> 51:39.891
Can we go?

52:05.918 --> 52:08.712
<i>You recall the guy who was drinking
by me, last time I was here?</i>

52:09.254 --> 52:12.758
I haven't seen him before or since.
He was probably just passing through.

52:26.772 --> 52:29.858
<i>You ain't owed nothing,
but you're getting a chance.</i>

52:32.444 --> 52:33.862
<i>Don't go driving now.</i>

52:47.042 --> 52:48.710
I thought I could help.

52:51.213 --> 52:53.048
Answer your question, you know.

52:55.133 --> 52:57.010
Yeah? What you think I'm wondering?

52:58.345 --> 52:59.345
"Why me?

53:00.681 --> 53:03.725
Why did God make or allow this to happen?"

53:04.309 --> 53:06.311
He doesn't promise
your stories will make sense,

53:06.395 --> 53:09.648
but he does promise
they'll find their greater purpose.

53:09.731 --> 53:10.858
If we're patient.

53:10.941 --> 53:11.941
Patient?

53:12.734 --> 53:14.069
You an expert on that.

53:22.160 --> 53:23.954
What's going on with you?

53:24.037 --> 53:26.582
Most things get squished on a road,
end up stuffed on a wall.

53:26.665 --> 53:28.250
I'm doing pretty good, considering.

53:28.333 --> 53:30.919
I know, but I'm concerned.

53:31.003 --> 53:33.046
I got a lot on my mind, all right?

53:35.716 --> 53:37.384
Let me help you take it off.

53:45.017 --> 53:46.018
Don't do this.

53:48.187 --> 53:49.521
I know what I'm doing.

53:58.447 --> 54:00.199
<i>Bless me, Father, for I have sinned.</i>

54:00.824 --> 54:03.660
It's been six weeks
since my last confession.

54:03.744 --> 54:04.745
I can't...

54:05.871 --> 54:08.874
I can't give you details on account
of there's a conflict of interest.

54:09.708 --> 54:12.628
The sacrament of confession is inviolable.

54:12.711 --> 54:15.088
I cannot, under pain of excommunication,

54:15.172 --> 54:18.091
reveal or act on
whatever it is you confess to me.

54:20.427 --> 54:23.055
I did something I ain't supposed to do.

54:24.640 --> 54:28.018
Something I been thinking about,
praying I could get to happen for months.

54:28.560 --> 54:31.480
Something I wanted
more than anything else in this world.

54:32.022 --> 54:35.609
Then I had it, and all I could do
was think about disappointing God.

54:35.692 --> 54:36.777
This is good news.

54:37.528 --> 54:40.405
It is
in discovering the greatness of God's love

54:40.489 --> 54:44.409
that our heart is shaken
by the horror and weight of sin.

54:44.493 --> 54:48.413
No, this ain't about fucking up.
It's about being fucked with.

54:50.582 --> 54:53.752
Another term for that is "grace."

54:53.836 --> 54:55.212
God's grace.

54:55.295 --> 54:57.548
It appears you are the recipient.

54:57.631 --> 54:59.675
What's he expecting me
to do with his grace?

54:59.758 --> 55:01.176
You could start by...

55:01.969 --> 55:03.220
cleaning up your language.

55:03.303 --> 55:06.098
Don't be a wise-ass, Father.
Answer the question.

55:07.307 --> 55:10.310
He expects you
to spread his word,

55:10.394 --> 55:11.687
advance his kingdom.

55:12.271 --> 55:14.606
He ain't making house calls asking that.

55:18.819 --> 55:20.779
He must have made a mistake.

55:20.863 --> 55:21.863
No.

55:23.115 --> 55:25.325
God doesn't make mistakes.

55:30.914 --> 55:34.209
Father G thinks maybe I could serve God.
You believe that shit?

55:35.836 --> 55:36.920
Like an altar boy?

55:37.004 --> 55:39.798
I've been thinking that
since the day I met you.

55:39.882 --> 55:41.216
- You have?
- No.

55:44.553 --> 55:46.972
But I'm sure he had good reason.

55:50.350 --> 55:52.477
My whole life,
I felt like I shouldn't be here.

55:52.561 --> 55:54.897
That my brother Stephen should instead.

55:56.023 --> 55:58.358
But after that night, I felt different.

55:59.568 --> 56:01.570
Like I might be good
for something after all.

56:03.280 --> 56:06.241
Perhaps the world needs
another Rhinestone Cowboy.

56:11.330 --> 56:14.166
I think
God saw something in you worth saving.

56:14.875 --> 56:18.003
But it's up to you
to decide what you've got to offer.

57:19.982 --> 57:22.359
I thought it'd make sense
being back here to do this.

57:22.943 --> 57:24.987
It's the place
you told me you believed in me.

57:33.871 --> 57:35.205
I'm gonna be a priest.

57:40.669 --> 57:41.670
What do you mean?

57:43.964 --> 57:46.175
It's five words.
I've practiced them a hundred times.

57:46.258 --> 57:47.509
What part is unclear?

57:49.094 --> 57:50.094
Every part.

57:51.972 --> 57:53.056
You're gonna be a priest?

57:53.140 --> 57:54.725
Stop saying it like that.

57:54.808 --> 57:56.602
Like what? Like it's insane?

57:56.685 --> 57:58.937
So was the idea
of the man upstairs pulling strings,

57:59.021 --> 58:01.148
but you bought that like a pair of shoes.

58:02.316 --> 58:05.527
God saved me and forgave me
to show me that there's a reason I'm here.

58:05.611 --> 58:07.738
We need to have your head examined.

58:07.821 --> 58:08.989
Trust me, Carmen.

58:09.072 --> 58:12.743
I tried every way to talk myself
out of it, but the truth is...

58:13.285 --> 58:15.078
I ain't never been more clear.

58:18.040 --> 58:20.250
Have you considered all this entails?

58:21.001 --> 58:23.629
Abstaining from booze and beatings,
not to mention sex?

58:23.712 --> 58:26.673
- You showed me I could do it.
- No, I showed you, you could wait.

58:26.757 --> 58:29.343
A vow of celibacy means never again.
Then you die.

58:29.426 --> 58:31.845
There's more to life than sex.
I can feel it.

58:31.929 --> 58:33.263
Most people know that.

58:33.347 --> 58:37.351
Only most people find
that other meaning in a passion,

58:37.434 --> 58:38.727
or people,

58:38.810 --> 58:40.103
or a family.

58:40.187 --> 58:42.814
- You're setting yourself up for failure.
- No.

58:42.898 --> 58:44.650
I been testing myself.

58:44.733 --> 58:48.820
If God's willing to forgive me,
I got to be willing to forgive others.

58:48.904 --> 58:51.281
Whoever hit me,
I wanted their dicks on a stick.

58:51.365 --> 58:53.742
But with God's help, I've forgiven them.

58:53.825 --> 58:56.411
And you think the absence
of the instinct to dismember someone

58:56.495 --> 58:58.747
qualifies you for priesthood?

58:58.830 --> 59:01.124
- You're delusional.
- Know what it takes to win a fight?

59:01.208 --> 59:05.254
You gotta turn off the animal brain,
use logic, humility, good judgment.

59:05.337 --> 59:08.632
That's the struggle of man.
I can do it. I can help.

59:10.926 --> 59:13.095
You got near death and found God.

59:13.679 --> 59:15.264
That's great, Stu, but...

59:17.057 --> 59:18.684
this is a little extreme.

59:18.767 --> 59:20.561
No, I didn't find him, Carmen.

59:21.144 --> 59:22.144
I felt him.

59:22.521 --> 59:25.315
I felt her. Mary.
Well, that don't sound...

59:25.399 --> 59:28.944
Look, the feeling she gave me,
I can't even explain it.

59:29.027 --> 59:32.781
For the first time in my life,
I knew I could stop fighting.

59:32.865 --> 59:35.158
I knew I was safe and loved.

59:47.212 --> 59:49.590
I disgraced myself before God,

59:50.507 --> 59:52.759
so that
you could have another flight of fancy.

59:52.843 --> 59:54.511
I know you're mad. Hit me if you want.

59:54.595 --> 59:56.763
- It'll make you feel better.
- I don't wanna hit you.

59:58.348 --> 59:59.683
I wanna marry you.

01:00:00.726 --> 01:00:03.395
I thought
that's what you brought me here for.

01:00:06.899 --> 01:00:07.899
I can't do that.

01:00:09.902 --> 01:00:10.902
I'm sorry.

01:00:12.613 --> 01:00:13.447
Carmen.

01:00:13.530 --> 01:00:14.530
Car...

01:00:15.616 --> 01:00:16.616
Damn.

01:00:23.665 --> 01:00:25.834
Your son is about to make a huge mistake.

01:00:25.918 --> 01:00:27.920
He don't usually warn no one,

01:00:28.003 --> 01:00:30.214
so I guess that's progress.

01:00:30.297 --> 01:00:33.050
You talked him out of boxing, right?

01:00:33.133 --> 01:00:34.133
Hey, Mama.

01:00:35.719 --> 01:00:38.055
Is someone gonna tell me what's going on?

01:00:38.138 --> 01:00:40.390
I was gonna find a better time.

01:00:40.974 --> 01:00:43.393
- You're doing a porno?
- No, God, no.

01:00:43.477 --> 01:00:45.020
No, I'm gonna be a priest.

01:00:46.355 --> 01:00:49.399
- For Halloween?
- No, not for fucking Halloween. For real.

01:00:50.776 --> 01:00:52.236
Oh, Stu.

01:00:52.319 --> 01:00:54.446
You can't be serious.

01:00:55.239 --> 01:00:56.073
This is your fault.

01:00:56.156 --> 01:00:58.867
You'd think I said
I wanted to be a serial killer.

01:00:58.951 --> 01:01:02.829
My son don't do half measures.
He's a dog with a goddamn bone.

01:01:02.913 --> 01:01:06.834
If you're so fucking enlightened,
you should've seen that.

01:01:08.252 --> 01:01:11.964
Had you been awake enough
to dignify his place in this world,

01:01:12.047 --> 01:01:14.550
in spite of the loss of your other son,

01:01:14.633 --> 01:01:17.177
he wouldn't be so desperate
to find himself.

01:01:17.261 --> 01:01:18.261
Baby, don't...

01:01:27.437 --> 01:01:28.564
I'm doing this.

01:01:35.654 --> 01:01:39.575
"To whom it may concern,
consider this application to the seminary.

01:01:39.658 --> 01:01:42.744
Enclosed you'll find my résumé,

01:01:42.828 --> 01:01:45.831
and half the fee.

01:01:45.914 --> 01:01:48.625
God will provide the rest cause."

01:01:48.709 --> 01:01:49.709
Cause?

01:01:50.919 --> 01:01:54.131
Oh, "'cause I'm praying for it."

01:01:56.091 --> 01:01:57.091
'Cause.

01:02:03.807 --> 01:02:05.350
Hey, Mama, I'm home.

01:02:05.434 --> 01:02:08.353
Hey, Stuart.
I just been admiring your artwork.

01:02:10.480 --> 01:02:13.192
- You invite him here?
- He came to check on you.

01:02:13.817 --> 01:02:16.737
You look about as holy as a healthy deuce.

01:02:17.362 --> 01:02:18.572
You had to tell him?

01:02:19.239 --> 01:02:21.783
- It's a sin to lie.
- You ain't the Catholic here.

01:02:21.867 --> 01:02:23.952
You've had some nutty ideas before,

01:02:24.036 --> 01:02:28.040
but this is like Hitler
asking to join the ADL.

01:02:28.123 --> 01:02:31.126
All these years, I was looking
for the wrong father's approval.

01:02:31.210 --> 01:02:32.461
I never needed yours.

01:02:32.544 --> 01:02:34.922
I always loved you
for the piece of shit you were.

01:02:35.005 --> 01:02:36.340
That's unconditional.

01:02:36.924 --> 01:02:37.924
It's obligation.

01:02:38.425 --> 01:02:39.801
You're punishing yourself.

01:02:39.885 --> 01:02:42.304
You've both been, since Stephen died.

01:02:42.387 --> 01:02:44.640
It's not punishment, it's purpose.

01:02:44.723 --> 01:02:47.059
Let me do one last thing as your dad.

01:02:47.809 --> 01:02:50.938
- Give you something you always wanted.
- What the fuck?

01:02:51.021 --> 01:02:53.732
You gonna disgrace me
and your brother like this,

01:02:53.815 --> 01:02:55.609
you might as well Bury me too.

01:02:58.111 --> 01:03:01.990
I'm turning my life around.
There ain't shit you could do to stop me.

01:03:02.074 --> 01:03:05.160
Unless you wanna shoot me.
Dine out on two dead kids.

01:03:05.244 --> 01:03:06.954
Oh, to hell with both of you.

01:03:07.037 --> 01:03:09.289
I trust we'll both find our way.

01:03:17.005 --> 01:03:19.383
You both better be gone when I get back.

01:04:29.953 --> 01:04:30.954
Excuse me, sir?

01:04:31.038 --> 01:04:32.664
Do you have an appointment?

01:04:33.290 --> 01:04:34.290
Yes.

01:04:36.543 --> 01:04:38.545
Take care, Jeff. All the best.

01:04:39.338 --> 01:04:40.339
Go on.

01:04:42.382 --> 01:04:43.382
Hey.

01:04:47.971 --> 01:04:50.766
- You're the IOU.
- You know something, Father?

01:04:50.849 --> 01:04:53.560
There's a sign on the wall
of my gym back home.

01:04:53.644 --> 01:04:56.772
"Hope is not a tactic."
I took that one to heart.

01:04:57.356 --> 01:04:59.816
Fought for everything I earned.
This ain't no different.

01:05:00.817 --> 01:05:04.988
I know what God's doing here.
Seeing how I respond, I don't get my way.

01:05:05.072 --> 01:05:06.990
I'd be red-assed about it.

01:05:07.574 --> 01:05:09.159
But I ain't giving up.

01:05:09.243 --> 01:05:11.203
Not on him or me.

01:05:12.204 --> 01:05:14.289
I want you to reconsider your rejection.

01:05:15.165 --> 01:05:18.585
There's nothing on your résumé
or in your references

01:05:18.669 --> 01:05:23.882
that speaks to behavioral conformity
with Catholic tradition.

01:05:24.842 --> 01:05:27.553
You are a pugilist with a criminal record.

01:05:27.636 --> 01:05:30.472
Look at St. Matthew,
St. Augustine, St. Francis.

01:05:30.556 --> 01:05:32.057
Some of the most remarkable figures

01:05:32.140 --> 01:05:34.518
in the history
of the Church are reformed men.

01:05:35.060 --> 01:05:38.105
Yes, but I think
what the Church needs now,

01:05:38.188 --> 01:05:39.188
more than ever,

01:05:39.648 --> 01:05:42.150
is to elevate the standard for a priest.

01:05:42.234 --> 01:05:44.820
No, the Church needs somebody
who's gonna fight for God.

01:05:44.903 --> 01:05:45.903
That's me.

01:05:46.321 --> 01:05:50.284
Besides, if the Church's choices don't
celebrate a person's capacity for change,

01:05:50.367 --> 01:05:52.327
then what else does it stand for?

01:05:53.579 --> 01:05:55.497
This may sound contradictory,

01:05:55.581 --> 01:05:59.293
but sometimes the best path to serving God

01:05:59.376 --> 01:06:02.087
is to step out of the way.

01:06:02.171 --> 01:06:05.048
With all due respect, monsignor,
you're getting in my way.

01:06:05.132 --> 01:06:06.633
God wants me here.

01:06:10.846 --> 01:06:15.100
Priests become the financial
responsibility of the Church.

01:06:15.184 --> 01:06:17.352
Now, by admitting you,

01:06:17.895 --> 01:06:20.981
we'd be agreeing to subsidize you

01:06:21.064 --> 01:06:23.483
as the face of Catholicism.

01:06:24.151 --> 01:06:27.863
Something our board
would be very reluctant to do.

01:06:27.946 --> 01:06:30.741
First it's admitting
you're afraid I'll succeed.

01:06:32.910 --> 01:06:35.913
If you so sure
I'll flame out, what you got to lose?

01:06:58.685 --> 01:07:00.646
- My man.
- Hey.

01:07:00.729 --> 01:07:02.314
Look at you. What?

01:07:02.397 --> 01:07:06.693
- The first of many inappropriate displays.
- Outward sign of inward grace.

01:07:06.777 --> 01:07:08.695
- And a hug from the heart.
- Hugs are healing.

01:07:08.779 --> 01:07:11.281
Jesus hugged a cripple,
that mother-hugger would walk.

01:07:11.365 --> 01:07:12.365
I need another one.

01:07:13.367 --> 01:07:16.495
Entering these gates, you surrender
any personal means of purchase.

01:07:16.578 --> 01:07:20.707
We rely on our sponsors for money.
You do have one of those, don't you?

01:07:20.791 --> 01:07:22.042
Don't worry about me.

01:07:22.125 --> 01:07:24.211
I been getting sponsorships
since I could swing.

01:07:26.046 --> 01:07:28.715
By the time I leave,
I'll have Jesus' name on my trunks.

01:07:29.424 --> 01:07:31.677
You can keep your driver's license
and insurance card.

01:07:31.760 --> 01:07:33.971
They took my license,
canceled my insurance.

01:07:34.054 --> 01:07:36.390
You doubted me, and I'm a step ahead.

01:07:36.473 --> 01:07:37.474
God bless you.

01:07:41.520 --> 01:07:43.397
It is my great privilege

01:07:43.480 --> 01:07:46.900
to welcome you
to the stewardship of theology.

01:07:46.984 --> 01:07:52.072
You are here to learn
that you will one day be a teacher.

01:07:52.155 --> 01:07:53.323
An advisor.

01:07:53.907 --> 01:07:55.200
A confessor.

01:07:55.784 --> 01:07:58.203
Indeed, a Father.

01:08:00.414 --> 01:08:01.415
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:08:09.131 --> 01:08:10.632
I guess we're gonna be roommates.

01:08:16.095 --> 01:08:17.220
Sixteen?

01:08:17.890 --> 01:08:18.890
Sixteen.

01:08:22.227 --> 01:08:24.104
They must've given me a faulty one.

01:08:24.188 --> 01:08:27.191
It's user error.
And it's like 2 in the morning.

01:08:27.274 --> 01:08:29.859
I ain't going down till I get this right.

01:08:29.943 --> 01:08:32.112
There is no MVP of Consecration.

